# Trivy Vulnerability Ignore List
#
# This file contains CVEs that are accepted as known upstream vulnerabilities
# that do not affect PostgreSQL functionality. See SECURITY.md for detailed justifications.

# CVE-2025-68121: Go stdlib crypto/tls session resumption — gosu in postgres base image layers
# - postgres:18.3-trixie ships gosu (Go 1.24.6) as a direct binary download (not a dpkg package)
# - The binary is in immutable base image layers; cannot be removed via apt or any Dockerfile instruction
# - /usr/local/bin/gosu is replaced by su-exec v0.2 (pure C, no Go stdlib) in the final build stage
# - Trivy scans ALL image layers including immutable base layers, finding gosu in the postgres base layer
# - In the merged filesystem (what containers actually see), su-exec is at that path — gosu is unreachable
# - Mitigation: gosu's Go binary is permanently shadowed; only su-exec is ever executed at runtime
# - See Fixed section in CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased] and Key Learnings in AGENTS.md
CVE-2025-68121

# CVE-2025-13836: Python http.client memory exhaustion vulnerability
# - PostgreSQL core is written in C and doesn't use Python
# - No enabled extensions use Python's http.client module
# - Python is present in base image but unused by PostgreSQL
# - Debian classified as minor issue (<no-dsa>)
# - Fixed in Python 3.13.11, awaiting Debian Trixie backport
# See SECURITY.md for full analysis
CVE-2025-13836
